X. Operator Algebra (Combinatorix Doctrine)

The alphabet forms a generative reasoning grammar.

Combinatorix governs:
	•	composition tables (legal move chains)
	•	invariant lattice (what survives transformations)
	•	equivalence classes (different moves with same effect)
	•	distortion accumulation metrics

This converts the alphabet into a true reasoning engine.

⸻

